\includegraphics[width=0.7\textwidth]{Ablation Remove L1 Loss and Macro F1 Curves.png}
\caption{\textbf{Remove L1 Penalty:} Also reaches near 0.80 but with less interpretability.}
\end{figure}

\begin{figure}[h!]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=0.7\textwidth]{Ablation Remove BoC Loss and Macro F1 Curves.png}
\caption{\textbf{Remove BoC:} Validation scores remain similar, indicating the complementary role of bag-of-characters.}
\end{figure}

\begin{figure}[h!]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=0.7\textwidth]{Ablation Freeze Embeddings Aggregate.png}
\caption{\textbf{Freeze Embeddings:} The model still converges quickly but shows potential overfitting to the training set.}
\end{figure}

\vspace{1em}
\noindent
\textbf{Code.} We provide a Python script (SPR.py) for data loading, along with training scripts in the supplementary materials. The proposed approach uses \texttt{datasets} for handling the SPR\_BENCH benchmark, ensuring reproducible experimental settings.

