\caption{\textbf{Overall Test Macro F1.} Baseline and our proposals achieve comparable performance ($\sim$0.80).}
\label{fig:overall_test}
\end{figure}

\section{Conclusion}
We investigated interpretable neural rule learning for the SPR task, showing that explicit rule representations can be integrated without severely impacting classification accuracy. While final F1 scores hover around 0.80, rule extraction reveals partial alignments with the underlying multi-factor logic. These results highlight persistent challenges in balancing transparency and modeling power. Future directions include rule composition for more complex reasoning patterns and improved regularization strategies to mitigate overfitting.

