Next, we incorporate the explicit rule layer. The final model (``Research'' approach) maintains a similar test F1 of $\sim0.797$, highlighting limited headroom in capturing more intricate rule interactions. \cref{fig:research_curves} shows fast training loss reduction but plateauing validation performance near 0.80. This plateau exemplifies a real-world pitfall: interpretability can be gained, but nuanced improvements remain elusive unless more robust mechanisms are introduced. \cref{fig:overall_test} summarizes the test Macro F1 across variations. 

