\section{Conclusion}
We investigated interpretable neural rule learning for SPR, finding that explicit rule representations can be integrated without severely impacting classification accuracy. Nonetheless, final F1 scores hover around 0.80, and the extracted rules only partially capture the multi-factor logic. Our results underscore the persistent challenge of reconciling interpretability and raw performance in complex tasks. From a practical standpoint, this underscores a pitfall commonly seen beyond benchmarks: overfitting or plateauing can limit gains in accuracy, even if interpretability is improved. Future work can consider more advanced symbolic components, additional regularization, or hierarchical rule composition to overcome these limitations.

