\section{Conclusion}
We investigated interpretable neural rule learning for SPR, finding that explicit rule representations can be integrated without significantly harming performance. However, the final F1 scores remain around 0.80, demonstrating that revealing interpretable structures does not necessarily boost raw accuracy on complex tasks. Our experiments emphasize the common pitfall of expecting interpretability to yield performance improvements automatically. Future directions include exploring more sophisticated rule-composition mechanisms and investigating richer symbolic priors to further align performance with the interpretability objective.

